text: Heli Lääts (24 June 1932 – 16 February 2018) was an Estonian singer (mezzo- soprano). Her career began in the mid-1950s. Lääts performed estrada, chamber, pop, polka, and jazz music. During her career, Lääts also recorded and performed a number of children's songs. She also released several albums, recorded music for Eesti Raadio, and recorded songs with Mikk Mikiver and Jaak Joala. Some of her best-known songs in Estonia include "Tsirkus," "Oma laulu ei leia ma üles," and "Tänav, pink ja puu."news.err.ee Singer Heli Lääts dies at 85 16 February 2018. Retrieved 18 February 2018. Lääts died at age 85 on 16 February 2018 in Tallinn. ==References== Category:1932 births Category:2018 deaths Category:Estonian singers Category:Pop singers
